Subject: BusFusion News

       BusFusionites, LAST CALL for BusFusion pre-registration !!  Deadline is
Monday May 26.  After that registrations that come in by mail, Internet or at
the gate may not get a BusFusion 2003 T-shirt and camping fees will be
$15/night, no discounts, so register NOW !
       The BusFusion website has been updated this morning with the new link
to RiverEdge - Celebrating the Arts in Mississippi Mills website.  More
Sponsors with more cool door prizes.  AND, more on the Lobster Fest & Sarah
Slean concert, reserve your tickets now before they are sold out, see the
website for details.
       Ray Knowls of the Ottawa Samba Drummers messaged me to let you all know
they will be there drumming away for your entertainment.
       Friday evening the RiverEdge Festival kicks off with an opening soiree,
the NFB film night, and a Jazz Crawl featuring three pubs and three great Jazz
groups for $10.  See the RiverEdge website and BusFusion Activities page for
more details.
       Saturday, RiverEdge has a full day of events to keep you spellbound.
Plus BusFusion will be having its giant VW Flea Market, bring your stuff to
sell & trade.  The BusFusion Van Painting, make a plan now.  The BusFusion Art
Show & Sale, bring your art work to show & sell.  And, the all VW Car Show !
       Looking forward to seeing you all at BusFusion 2003 !

Cheers

Frank Condelli
